\[ 0.35 - 0.15 = 0.20 \]
Expressing 0.20 as a percentage, we get:
\[ 0.20 \times 100\% = 20\% \]

Therefore, it is \(\boxed{20}\) percent more likely that Andy loses both lawsuits compared to winning both of them. 
