Now, we calculate the weekly production by multiplying the daily production by the number of days in a week (7 days):

\[
11 \text{ pails/day} \times 7 \text{ days/week} = 77 \text{ pails/week}
\]

Thus, Farmer Red gets \(\boxed{77}\) pails of milk from his three cows each week. 
