The total time spent on all tasks can be expressed as the sum of the time spent on each individual task:
\[ 30 + 15 + t + 40 = 120 \]

Now we can solve for \( t \):
\[ 85 + t = 120 \]
\[ t = 120 - 85 \]
\[ t = 35 \]

So, Miriam spent \(\boxed{35}\) minutes cleaning her room. 
