\[ 240 - 170 = 70 \text{ degrees} \]
Since the candy cools at a rate of 7 degrees per minute, the time required to cool the candy is:
\[ \frac{70}{7} = 10 \text{ minutes} \]

The total time required to complete the process is the sum of the heating time and the cooling time:
\[ 36 + 10 = 46 \text{ minutes} \]

Therefore, the total time it takes for the candy to be done is:
\[ \boxed{46} \] 
