\]

Now, we sum the corn cobs from both fields to find the total number of corn cobs grown on the farm:
\[
\text{Total number of corn cobs} = 52 \text{ corn cobs} + 64 \text{ corn cobs} = 116 \text{ corn cobs}
\]

Thus, the farm has grown \boxed{116} corn cobs. 
