   Since there are 30 days in the month, we multiply the number of visits per day by the number of days:
   \[
   \text{Visits per month} = \text{Visits per day} \times \text{Days per month} = 1200 \times 30 = 36000
   \]

5. **Calculate the amount of money Jon makes per visit:**
   Jon gets paid $0.10 for each visit.

6. **Calculate the total amount of money made in a month:**
   \[
   \text{Total earnings} = \text{Visits per month} \times \text{Payment per visit} = 36000 \times 0.10 = 3600
   \]

