A bathroom has 10 6 inch tiles along its width and 20 6 inch tiles along its length.  What is the square footage of the bathroom? 
Response:
To find the square footage of the bathroom, we need to determine the area of the floor by calculating the product of its width and length in square inches, and then convert that area into square feet.

First, we calculate the width of the bathroom in inches:
\[
10 \text{ tiles} \times 6 \text{ inches/tile} = 60 \text{ inches}
\]

Next, we calculate the length of the bathroom in inches:
\[
20 \text{ tiles} \times 6 \text{ inches/tile} = 120 \text{ inches}
\]

To find the area in square inches, we multiply the width by the length:
\[
60 \text{ inches} \times 120 \text{ inches} = 7200 \text{ square inches}
\]

Now we need to convert the area from square inches to square feet. We know that 1 square foot is equal to 144 square inches (since \(12 \text{ inches} \times 12 \text{ inches} = 144 \text{ square inches}\)).

To find the area in square feet, we divide the area in square inches by 144:
\[
7200 \text{ square inches} \div 144 \text{ square inches/square foot} = 50 \text{ square feet}
\]

Therefore, the square footage of the bathroom is \(\boxed{50}\). 
