1. **Calculate Lulu's savings:**
   Lulu has saved $6.
   \[
   \text{Lulu's savings} = \$6
   \]

2. **Calculate Nora's savings:**
   Nora has saved five times what Lulu has.
   \[
   \text{Nora's savings} = 5 \times \text{Lulu's savings} = 5 \times \$6 = \$30
   \]

