Next, we need to determine how much Susie spent on the make-up set. She spent \(\frac{3}{10}\) of her total earnings on the make-up set.
\[
\text{Amount spent on make-up set} = \frac{3}{10} \times 210 \text{ dollars} = 63 \text{ dollars}
\]

