\[
\frac{2}{3} \times 3 = 2 \text{ liters}
\]

After drinking 2 liters of water, the amount of water left in the bottle is:

\[
3 - 2 = 1 \text{ liter}
\]

Thus, the amount of water left in the bottle is:

