\[
\text{Rate} = \frac{3 \text{ whiteboards}}{20 \text{ minutes}} = \frac{3}{20} \text{ whiteboards per minute per kid}
\]
So, each kid washes:
\[
\text{Rate per kid} = \frac{3}{20 \times 4} = \frac{3}{80} \text{ whiteboards per minute}
\]

Now, we need to find out how long it takes for one kid to wash six whiteboards. We use the rate we just calculated:
\[
\text{Time for one kid to wash six whiteboards} = \frac{\text{Total number of whiteboards}}{\text{Rate per kid}} = \frac{6}{\frac{3}{80}} = 6 \times \frac{80}{3} = 160 \text{ minutes}
\]

Thus, it would take one kid 160 minutes to wash six whiteboards. The final answer is:
\[
\boxed{160}
\] 
