   Marcus has 2 $10 bills.
   \[
   \text{Total money Marcus has} = 2 \times 10 \text{ dollars} = 20 \text{ dollars}
   \]

5. **Calculate the change Marcus will have after the purchase:**
   Subtract the total cost of the water from the total money Marcus has.
   \[
   \text{Change} = 20 \text{ dollars} - 15 \text{ dollars} = 5 \text{ dollars}
   \]

