\[ \text{Weight on the day of the fight} = \text{Initial weight} - \text{Total weight loss} = 97 \, \text{kg} - 12 \, \text{kg} = 85 \, \text{kg} \]

Therefore, the boxer will weigh \(\boxed{85}\) kg on the day of the fight. 
