   Kara read half the number of books that Amanda read. So:
   \[
   \text{Number of books Kara read} = \frac{6}{2} = 3
   \]

4. Determine the number of books Patricia read.
   Patricia read 7 times the number of books that Kara read. So:
   \[
   \text{Number of books Patricia read} = 7 \times 3 = 21
   \]

