   \[
   \text{Leftover money after taxes} = 12006 - 6003 = 6003
   \]

3. **Calculate the money spent on student loans:**
   Marge put a third of the leftover money towards her student loans.
   \[
   \text{Loan amount} = \frac{6003}{3} = 2001
   \]

4. **Calculate the leftover money after paying student loans:**
   \[
   \text{Leftover money after loans} = 6003 - 2001 = 4002
   \]

5. **Calculate the money put into savings:**
   Marge put $1000 in savings.

