\[ 2Y + Y = 6 \]
\[ 3Y = 6 \]
\[ Y = 2 \]

Now that we know \( Y = 2 \), we can substitute this value back into the first equation to find \( B \):

\[ B = 2Y \]
\[ B = 2 \times 2 \]
\[ B = 4 \]

So, the number of blue butterflies Martha has is \(\boxed{4}\). 
