\[
\text{Average speed} = \frac{\text{Total distance}}{\text{Total time}}
\]

Substituting the known values into the formula, we get:

\[
\text{Average speed} = \frac{693 \text{ miles}}{11 \text{ hours}} = 63 \text{ miles per hour}
\]

Therefore, the average minimum speed that Andy needs to drive to reach Los Angeles in 11 hours is:

