\[ (2A + B) - (A + B) = 7 - 5 \]
\[ 2A + B - A - B = 2 \]
\[ A = 2 \]

Now that we have \( A = 2 \), we can substitute this value back into the second equation to find \( B \):

\[ A + B = 5 \]
\[ 2 + B = 5 \]
\[ B = 3 \]

So, the cost of a bunch of bananas is \(\boxed{3}\). 
