\[ \text{Time for John} = \frac{5 \text{ miles}}{15 \text{ mph}} = \frac{5}{15} \text{ hours} = \frac{1}{3} \text{ hours} \]

Next, we need to convert this time from hours to minutes. There are 60 minutes in an hour, so we multiply by 60:
\[ \text{Time for John in minutes} = \frac{1}{3} \text{ hours} \times 60 \text{ minutes/hour} = 20 \text{ minutes} \]

The next fastest guy finished the race in 23 minutes. To find out how many minutes John won the race by, we subtract John's time from the next fastest guy's time:
\[ \text{Minutes by which John won} = 23 \text{ minutes} - 20 \text{ minutes} = 3 \text{ minutes} \]

Therefore, John won the race by \(\boxed{3}\) minutes. 
