   Each braid takes 30 seconds. Therefore, the total time in seconds to braid all 40 braids is:
   \[
   40 \text{ braids} \times 30 \text{ seconds per braid} = 1200 \text{ seconds}
   \]

3. **Convert the total time from seconds to minutes:**
   There are 60 seconds in a minute. To convert 1200 seconds to minutes, we divide by 60:
   \[
   \frac{1200 \text{ seconds}}{60 \text{ seconds per minute}} = 20 \text{ minutes}
   \]

Thus, the total time it will take Jill to braid all the dancers' hair is \(\boxed{20}\) minutes. 
