The cost to make each gallon of lemonade is $3.50, and he made 2 gallons.
\[ 2 \text{ gallons} \times 3.50 \text{ dollars/gallon} = 7 \text{ dollars} \]

**Step 3: Calculate the total number of glasses sold.**

Brad decided to sell all but 6 glasses of lemonade.
\[ 32 \text{ glasses} - 6 \text{ glasses} = 26 \text{ glasses} \]

Each glass is sold for $1.00, so the total revenue from selling 26 glasses is:
\[ 26 \text{ glasses} \times 1 \text{ dollar/glass} = 26 \text{ dollars} \]

**Step 4: Subtract the total cost from the total revenue to find the net profit.**

The net profit is the total revenue minus the total cost.
\[ 26 \text{ dollars} - 7 \text{ dollars} = 19 \text{ dollars} \]

Therefore, Brad's net profit is \(\boxed{19}\). 
