For the burritos:
\[ \text{Calories per dollar} = \frac{1200 \text{ calories}}{6 \text{ dollars}} = 200 \text{ calories per dollar} \]

For the burgers:
\[ \text{Calories per dollar} = \frac{2000 \text{ calories}}{8 \text{ dollars}} = 250 \text{ calories per dollar} \]

**Step 4: Determine the difference in calories per dollar between the burgers and the burritos.**

The difference is:
\[ 250 \text{ calories per dollar} - 200 \text{ calories per dollar} = 50 \text{ calories per dollar} \]

Thus, John gets \(\boxed{50}\) more calories per dollar from the burgers compared to the burritos. 
