   The rest of the tables have 4 chairs each. Since there are 32 tables in total and 16 of them have 2 chairs and 5 have 3 chairs, the number of tables with 4 chairs is:
   \[
   32 - 16 - 5 = 11 \text{ tables}
   \]
   Each of these 11 tables has 4 chairs, so the total number of chairs from these tables is:
   \[
   11 \times 4 = 44 \text{ chairs}
   \]

4. **Calculate the total number of chairs in the hall:**
   We add up the chairs from all the tables:
   \[
   32 + 15 + 44 = 91
   \]

