   \[
   \text{Number of seats sold} = 0.75 \times 60,000
   \]
   \[
   \text{Number of seats sold} = 45,000
   \]

2. **Calculate the number of fans who attended the show:**
   According to the problem, 5,000 fans stayed home due to the threat of rain. Therefore, the number of fans who attended the show is the total number of seats sold minus the number of fans who stayed home.
   \[
   \text{Number of fans who attended} = 45,000 - 5,000
   \]
   \[
   \text{Number of fans who attended} = 40,000
   \]

Thus, the number of fans who attended the show is \(\boxed{40000}\). 97%|█████████▋| 1812/1868 [2:08:31<03:55,  4.21s/it]